<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 01:15:01 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>物理学家：我相信你可以增强你的意识——并将你的感知扩展到“不同的领域”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/physicist-i-believe-you-can-enhance-your-consciousness-and-expand-your-perception-into-a-different-realm</link><description>但如果我们的生物构成限制了我们的创造力怎么办？也许控制我们内省的时钟的时间安排迫使我们的直觉时期——或者不确定的时期——变得太短暂。我们可以利用量子技术来扩展大脑内部的波状处理吗？我在这里受到奥尔德斯·赫胥黎（Aldous Huxley）的启发，他在他的名著中建议： &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/physicist-i-believe-you-can-enhance-your-consciousness-and-expand-your-perception-into-a-different-realm.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 01:14:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/physicist-i-believe-you-can-enhance-your-consciousness-and-expand-your-perception-into-a-different-realm</guid></item><item><title>对于小行星撞击地球你应该有多担心？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/how-worried-should-you-be-about-an-asteroid-smashing-into-earth</link><description>在寒冷的太空深处的某个地方，有一块太空岩石可能会摧毁地球上的大部分生命。难道这样的命运是不可避免的吗？我们能否找到一种方法来阻止它，或者我们最终会遭受与恐龙相同的命运？这种生存威胁会让你彻夜难眠吗？这是我们所知道的。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-worried-should-you-be-about-an-asteroid-smashing-into-earth.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:59:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/how-worried-should-you-be-about-an-asteroid-smashing-into-earth</guid></item><item><title>癌细胞脂型与疾病状态之间的相互作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/interplay-between-cancer-cell-lipotypes-and-disease-states</link><description>癌症中的脂质代谢。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/interplay-between-cancer-cell-lipotypes-and-disease-states2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:44:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/interplay-between-cancer-cell-lipotypes-and-disease-states</guid></item><item><title>识别气味受体贩运中的关键调节剂</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/identifying-key-regulators-in-odorant-receptor-trafficking</link><description>JNeurosci：Lu 和 Matsunami 分析了基因活性，以找到有助于气味检测受体到达细胞表面的蛋白质。他们确定了三个辅助基因——Gfy、Clgn 和 Syt1——在嗅觉细胞成熟时支持受体功能。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/identifying-key-regulators-in-odorant-receptor-trafficking2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:29:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/identifying-key-regulators-in-odorant-receptor-trafficking</guid></item><item><title>一题筛查可能会发现阿尔茨海默氏症和其他痴呆症患者的囤积行为</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/one-question-screen-may-flag-hoarding-in-alzheimers-and-other-dementias</link><description>科罗拉多大学安舒茨分校的研究人员开发了一种简单的单问题筛查工具，可以帮助医生快速识别记忆丧失和其他脑部疾病患者的囤积行为。他们说，早期发现可以导致早期干预，有助于降低安全风险、减轻护理人员的压力并改善患者和家人的生活质量。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/one-question-screen-may-flag-hoarding-in-alzheimers-and-other-dementias.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:14:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/one-question-screen-may-flag-hoarding-in-alzheimers-and-other-dementias</guid></item><item><title>工程蛋白质标记通过血液读取猴子活体大脑基因活动</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/engineered-protein-markers-read-living-brain-gene-activity-in-monkeys-via-blood</link><description>基因疗法已成功用于治疗多种疾病，包括免疫缺陷、遗传性失明、血友病以及最近的亨廷顿病（一种致命的神经系统疾病）。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/engineered-protein-markers-read-living-brain-gene-activity-in-monkeys-via-blood.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 23:59:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/engineered-protein-markers-read-living-brain-gene-activity-in-monkeys-via-blood</guid></item><item><title>ALS 疾病进展过程中自然杀伤细胞失调基因表达分析</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/natural-killer-cell-dysregulation-during-als-disease-progressiona-gene-expression-analysis</link><description>研究发现，随着肌萎缩侧索硬化症 (ALS) 的进展，自然杀伤 (NK) 细胞的生长更加失调，并表现出 2 型极化或免疫衰竭的特征。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/natural-killer-cell-dysregulation-during-als-disease-progressiona-gene-expression-analysis2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 23:44:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/natural-killer-cell-dysregulation-during-als-disease-progressiona-gene-expression-analysis</guid></item><item><title>生物工程神经元“电路板”模仿人脑的条件</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/bioengineered-neuronal-circuit-board-mimics-conditions-of-the-human-brain</link><description>新型生物工程神经元电路板“BioConNet”使科学家能够大规模人工设计类似人脑的线路，并可用于设计任何可能的电路。完全可编程的开源系统允许生成大规模电路，同时保持专注于神经元之间的单个连接的能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/bioengineered-neuronal-circuit-board-mimics-conditions-of-the-human-brain.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 23:29:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/bioengineered-neuronal-circuit-board-mimics-conditions-of-the-human-brain</guid></item><item><title>视网膜整个带状突触的高压冷冻 EM 断层扫描</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/high-pressure-freezing-em-tomography-of-entire-ribbon-synapses-in-the-retina</link><description>JNeurosci：Zhang 等人在大鼠中使用先进的电子显微镜。捕获了在视网膜中执行视觉计算的化学突触的 3D 图像。他们的发现揭示了神经连接是如何构建有效的视觉信号的。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/high-pressure-freezing-em-tomography-of-entire-ribbon-synapses-in-the-retina2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 23:14:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/high-pressure-freezing-em-tomography-of-entire-ribbon-synapses-in-the-retina</guid></item><item><title>突发事件：一股黑暗神秘力量刚刚撕裂银河系</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/breaking-a-dark-mysterious-force-just-ripped-across-the-milky-way</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 22:59:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/breaking-a-dark-mysterious-force-just-ripped-across-the-milky-way</guid></item></channel></rss>